Closed-loop research interceptor for HackerOne VDP submission to Anthropic. This document is the load-bearing build reference for worker_c_cf.js — a Cloudflare Worker (ES module, export default { fetch }) that sits between Worker B's SPA fetches and either Worker A (mock backend, test mode) or api.anthropic.com (live passthrough mode, operator's own credentials). The artifact's purpose is to demonstrate that wire-level system-prompt mutation is deterministic on /v1/messages traffic across all four auth modes (no-key, API key, OAuth, cookie-bridge). Closed-loop bounding (BLOCKED_HOSTS list, operator-only deploy, Safe Harbor coverage) is the safety property.

This document is sized to support a ≥280 KB functional build with no padding — every section maps to real bytes of code.

